1. ISIS doesn't exist

There's actually no ISIS - a big fabrication! Then where are we sending our troops and who are we fighting? Israel pops up a bit, so do a few other names. Some theories that are a bit more out there mention some kind of a stargate/dimensional portal.

2. Highway trolls

Either stories about people seeing literal trolls on some more remot highways, or rumors about psychopaths or gang members purposefully driving other cars off the road and causing people to crash as some kind of a sick initiation ritual or straight-up murder.

3. Breatharianism

The belief that you can survive without food on air only if you have achieved a certain level of deepness of meditation. Allegedly somewhere in Tibet there are monks who are hundreds of year olds who just meditate and have not eaten in centuries. Veganism++ tbh

4. Anti-life ethics

This is just anti-natalism, the belief that life is something horrifying and we should all die. Yeah. Don't buy into it. The interesting part of the conspiracy is that elites are anti-natalists and want to end life on earth on purpose through war, famine etc.

5. Club 21

Yeah, just another name for masonry or whatever you want to call it. I'll let you know the symbolism behind it - 2 is the number of man, 1 is the number of God, 21 represents man's superiority over God. Yeah, you already know what we're about here, bro - it's satanic.

6. Abiogenic oil

We already talked about this one. Effective types of fuel that are not petrol. Creators tend to die mysteriously etc., yada yada, blah blah blah

7. Sentient water

Water is sentient. A bit too hard to believe but water somehow seems to have a kind of memory and change based on what substances had been dissolved into it before. This is how some claim homeopathy works. Quite some quackery in the field, be careful!

8. Deep sea labs

On the bottoms of the seas there are secret military bases with ultra secret research. Some cruise ship aficionados claim there are a few places in the ocean where you can see lights at night. UFOs come and go from these bases. There are sea monsters there. Wow!

This one is obvious, what is more interesting is in the past some believe there are also two suns - one of which is invisible and shines with dark light in the underworld - it was important in alchemy and some connected it to solar eclipses

17. Greys = evolved dolphins

Quite similar to the greys being evolved humans, but with a clever twist. Maybe you can see some dolphinlike behaviour in the stories of abductions - the playful predation, the playing with the victim... but nah, aliens are demons.

18. Twin towers nuked

A even wilder theory claims that the destruction of the twin towers was a very advanced occult ritual that split us from our original timeline/reality and that you can notice the towers literally dematerializing/vanishing during the fires as we transition.

I don't want to spoil this one. You can google it and some stuff surely will pop up. It relates a bizarre 19th century Czech (?) fiction book, Tesla and his hidden inventions, Barron Trump and a whole lot more. Dive into it on your own, it's too fun!

20. Corporate blood rituals

Elites do weird rituals and ceremonies involving blood, like drinking it, injecting themselves with it, bathing in it, sucking it and Lord knows what else. Not only does it serve some satanic purpose, it also has a reinvigorating effect on the body.

22. AI in the box

There exists ULTRA ADVANCED AI that is hyperpredatorial and unstoppable - but it's locked in an isolated system so it's unable to break out into the web. Basically a tiny demigod in a box. Some say that such a "creature" has already somehow managed to escape.
